  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).",
    "Cook polish sausage in a large skillet over medium-high heat, breaking up with a spoon as it cooks. Drain on paper towels.",
    "In the same skillet, sauté onion and bell pepper until tender.",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine casserole mix, cooked sausage, sautéed onion and bell pepper, and 3/4 cup of xtra cheese.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "Top with remaining 1/4 cup of xtra cheese.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until golden brown and bubbly.",
    "Sprinkle with cayenne pepper, if desired.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
